    metaDesc: 'Calculate your net salary after income tax and social security in 15 European countries. Uses 2026 tax brackets for Germany, France, Netherlands, Spain, and more.',
    home: 'Home',
    breadcrumbCalc: 'Calculator',
    breadcrumb: 'Net Salary',
    introAnswer: 'Our net salary calculator instantly converts your gross annual salary into take-home pay for any of 15 European countries. It applies 2026 income tax brackets and social security rates so you can compare what you actually keep across borders.',
    tldr: [
      'Covers 15 EU countries with 2026 income tax brackets and social security contribution rates',
      'Supports three filing statuses: single, married, and married with children',
      'Instant results showing gross salary, income tax, social security, and net take-home pay',
    ],
    calcTitle: 'Calculate Your Net Salary',
    calcDesc: 'Select a country, enter your gross annual salary, and choose your filing status. Results update instantly.',
    countryLabel: 'Country',
    countryPlaceholder: 'Select a country',
    grossLabel: 'Gross Annual Salary',
    grossPlaceholder: '50000',
    statusLabel: 'Filing Status',
    statusSingle: 'Single',
    statusMarried: 'Married',
    statusMarriedChildren: 'Married with children',
    calculateBtn: 'Calculate Net Salary',
    resultGross: 'Gross Salary',
    resultIncomeTax: 'Income Tax',
    resultSocial: 'Social Security',
    resultNet: 'Net Salary (Take-Home)',
    resultTitle: 'Your Results',
    breakdownTitle: 'Salary Breakdown',
    compareTitle: 'How Does This Compare to Other Countries?',
    compareDesc: 'The same gross salary yields very different net pay across Europe. Tax regimes, social contribution rates, and deductions vary significantly. Use the calculator above with different countries to compare directly, or visit our country comparison pages for detailed analysis.',
    disclaimerTitle: 'Important Disclaimer',
    disclaimerText: 'This calculator provides estimates based on simplified 2026 tax brackets and standard social security rates. Actual net pay may differ due to local surcharges, church tax, regional variations, personal deductions, and employer-specific contributions. For precise calculations, consult a local tax advisor. EuroSalary does not provide tax or legal advice.',
    faq: [
      { question: 'How accurate is this net salary calculator?', answer: 'The calculator uses simplified 2026 tax brackets and standard employee social security contribution rates for each country. It provides a reliable estimate for planning purposes but does not account for local surcharges (e.g., German Solidaritaetszuschlag), church tax, municipal variations, or personal deductions. For exact figures, consult a certified tax advisor in the relevant country.' },
      { question: 'Which tax year do the brackets reflect?', answer: 'All tax brackets and social security rates are based on 2026 legislation as published by each country\'s tax authority or finance ministry. We update brackets annually when new rates are officially announced, typically in Q4 of the preceding year.' },
      { question: 'Does the filing status affect the tax calculation?', answer: 'Yes. In most European countries, married filers benefit from income splitting or joint assessment, which can lower the effective tax rate. The married with children status applies additional child-related deductions or credits where applicable. The exact benefit varies by country.' },
      { question: 'Why does the same gross salary result in very different net pay across countries?', answer: 'European countries have vastly different tax structures. Some like Denmark have high income tax but lower social contributions. Others like France have moderate income tax but high social security charges. Additionally, tax brackets, allowances, and deduction rules differ. Our comparison pages help you understand these differences in detail.' },
      { question: 'Can I use this calculator for monthly salary calculations?', answer: 'The calculator works with annual gross salary. To estimate monthly take-home pay, divide the annual net result by 12. Note that some countries (e.g., Spain, Italy, Portugal) commonly pay 14 monthly salaries instead of 12, which affects per-month calculations but not the annual total.' },
    ],
  },
  fr: {
    h1: 'Combien garderez-vous apres impots en Europe ?',
    metaTitle: 'Calculateur de salaire net : revenu apres impots dans 15 pays de l\'UE | EuroSalary.eu',
    metaDesc: 'Calculez votre salaire net apres impot sur le revenu et cotisations sociales dans 15 pays europeens. Utilise les baremes fiscaux 2026 pour l\'Allemagne, la France, les Pays-Bas, l\'Espagne et plus.',
    home: 'Accueil',
    breadcrumbCalc: 'Calculateur',
    breadcrumb: 'Salaire Net',
    introAnswer: 'Notre calculateur de salaire net convertit instantanement votre salaire annuel brut en revenu net pour 15 pays europeens. Il applique les baremes d\'impot sur le revenu et les taux de cotisations sociales 2026 pour comparer ce que vous gardez reellement.',
    tldr: [
      'Couvre 15 pays de l\'UE avec les baremes fiscaux 2026 et les taux de cotisations sociales',
      'Trois statuts de declaration : celibataire, marie, et marie avec enfants',
      'Resultats instantanes affichant salaire brut, impot sur le revenu, cotisations sociales et salaire net',
    ],
    calcTitle: 'Calculez votre salaire net',
    calcDesc: 'Selectionnez un pays, entrez votre salaire annuel brut et choisissez votre statut. Les resultats s\'affichent instantanement.',
    countryLabel: 'Pays',
    countryPlaceholder: 'Selectionnez un pays',
    grossLabel: 'Salaire annuel brut',
    grossPlaceholder: '50000',
    statusLabel: 'Statut de declaration',
    statusSingle: 'Celibataire',
    statusMarried: 'Marie(e)',
    statusMarriedChildren: 'Marie(e) avec enfants',
    calculateBtn: 'Calculer le salaire net',
    resultGross: 'Salaire brut',
    resultIncomeTax: 'Impot sur le revenu',
    resultSocial: 'Cotisations sociales',
    resultNet: 'Salaire net (revenu percu)',
    resultTitle: 'Vos resultats',
    breakdownTitle: 'Repartition du salaire',
    compareTitle: 'Comment cela se compare-t-il aux autres pays ?',
    compareDesc: 'Le meme salaire brut donne un salaire net tres different selon les pays europeens. Les regimes fiscaux, les taux de cotisations sociales et les deductions varient considerablement. Utilisez le calculateur ci-dessus avec differents pays pour comparer directement.',
    disclaimerTitle: 'Avertissement important',
    disclaimerText: 'Ce calculateur fournit des estimations basees sur les baremes fiscaux simplifies de 2026 et les taux standard de cotisations sociales. Le salaire net reel peut differer en raison de surtaxes locales, d\'impots regionaux, de deductions personnelles et de contributions specifiques a l\'employeur. Consultez un conseiller fiscal local pour des calculs precis.',
    faq: [
      { question: 'Quelle est la precision de ce calculateur de salaire net ?', answer: 'Le calculateur utilise les baremes fiscaux simplifies 2026 et les taux standard de cotisations sociales. Il fournit une estimation fiable pour la planification mais ne tient pas compte des surtaxes locales, de l\'impot religieux ou des deductions personnelles. Consultez un conseiller fiscal certifie pour des chiffres exacts.' },
      { question: 'Quelle annee fiscale les baremes refletent-ils ?', answer: 'Tous les baremes et taux sont bases sur la legislation 2026 publiee par les autorites fiscales de chaque pays. Nous mettons a jour annuellement quand les nouveaux taux sont officiellement annonces.' },
      { question: 'Le statut de declaration affecte-t-il le calcul ?', answer: 'Oui. Dans la plupart des pays europeens, les couples maries beneficient du quotient familial ou de l\'imposition conjointe. Le statut marie avec enfants applique des deductions supplementaires liees aux enfants.' },
      { question: 'Pourquoi le meme salaire brut donne-t-il un net tres different selon les pays ?', answer: 'Les pays europeens ont des structures fiscales tres differentes. Certains comme le Danemark ont un impot eleve mais des cotisations faibles. D\'autres comme la France ont un impot modere mais des charges sociales elevees.' },
      { question: 'Puis-je utiliser ce calculateur pour un salaire mensuel ?', answer: 'Le calculateur fonctionne avec le salaire annuel brut. Pour estimer le revenu mensuel net, divisez le resultat annuel par 12. Notez que certains pays versent 14 mensualites au lieu de 12.' },
    ],
  },
  de: {
    h1: 'Wie viel bleibt Ihnen nach Steuern in Europa ubrig?',
    metaTitle: 'Nettogehaltsrechner: Nettolohn in 15 EU-Landern | EuroSalary.eu',
    metaDesc: 'Berechnen Sie Ihr Nettogehalt nach Einkommensteuer und Sozialabgaben in 15 europaischen Landern. Verwendet die Steuertarife 2026 fur Deutschland, Frankreich, Niederlande, Spanien und mehr.',
    home: 'Startseite',
    breadcrumbCalc: 'Rechner',
    breadcrumb: 'Nettogehalt',
    introAnswer: 'Unser Nettogehaltsrechner rechnet Ihr Bruttojahresgehalt sofort in den Nettolohn fur 15 europaische Lander um. Er wendet die Einkommensteuertarife und Sozialversicherungssatze 2026 an, damit Sie vergleichen konnen, was Sie tatsachlich behalten.',
    tldr: [
      'Deckt 15 EU-Lander mit Einkommensteuertarifen 2026 und Sozialversicherungssatzen ab',
      'Drei Veranlagungsarten: ledig, verheiratet und verheiratet mit Kindern',
      'Sofortige Ergebnisse mit Bruttogehalt, Einkommensteuer, Sozialabgaben und Nettogehalt',
    ],
    calcTitle: 'Berechnen Sie Ihr Nettogehalt',
    calcDesc: 'Wahlen Sie ein Land, geben Sie Ihr Bruttojahresgehalt ein und wahlen Sie Ihren Veranlagungsstatus. Die Ergebnisse werden sofort angezeigt.',
    countryLabel: 'Land',
    countryPlaceholder: 'Land auswahlen',
    grossLabel: 'Bruttojahresgehalt',
    grossPlaceholder: '50000',
    statusLabel: 'Veranlagungsstatus',
    statusSingle: 'Ledig',
    statusMarried: 'Verheiratet',
    statusMarriedChildren: 'Verheiratet mit Kindern',
    calculateBtn: 'Nettogehalt berechnen',
    resultGross: 'Bruttogehalt',
    resultIncomeTax: 'Einkommensteuer',
    resultSocial: 'Sozialabgaben',
    resultNet: 'Nettogehalt (Auszahlung)',
    resultTitle: 'Ihre Ergebnisse',
    breakdownTitle: 'Gehaltsaufschlusselung',
    compareTitle: 'Wie schneidet dies im Vergleich zu anderen Landern ab?',
    compareDesc: 'Das gleiche Bruttogehalt ergibt in Europa sehr unterschiedliche Nettogehalter. Steuersysteme, Sozialabgabensatze und Abzuge variieren erheblich. Verwenden Sie den Rechner oben mit verschiedenen Landern zum direkten Vergleich.',
    disclaimerTitle: 'Wichtiger Hinweis',
    disclaimerText: 'Dieser Rechner liefert Schatzungen auf Basis vereinfachter Steuertarife 2026 und Standard-Sozialversicherungssatze. Das tatsachliche Nettogehalt kann aufgrund lokaler Zuschlage, Kirchensteuer, regionaler Unterschiede und personlicher Abzuge abweichen. Fur prazise Berechnungen wenden Sie sich an einen Steuerberater.',
    faq: [
      { question: 'Wie genau ist dieser Nettogehaltsrechner?', answer: 'Der Rechner verwendet vereinfachte Steuertarife 2026 und Standard-Sozialversicherungssatze. Er liefert eine zuverlassige Schatzung fur Planungszwecke, berucksichtigt aber keine lokalen Zuschlage, Kirchensteuer oder personliche Abzuge.' },
      { question: 'Welches Steuerjahr spiegeln die Tarife wider?', answer: 'Alle Steuertarife und Sozialversicherungssatze basieren auf der Gesetzgebung 2026. Wir aktualisieren die Tarife jahrlich, wenn neue Satze offiziell bekanntgegeben werden.' },
      { question: 'Beeinflusst der Veranlagungsstatus die Berechnung?', answer: 'Ja. In den meisten europaischen Landern profitieren Verheiratete vom Ehegattensplitting oder gemeinsamer Veranlagung. Der Status verheiratet mit Kindern wendet zusatzliche Kinderfreibetrage an.' },
      { question: 'Warum ergibt das gleiche Bruttogehalt in verschiedenen Landern ein sehr unterschiedliches Nettogehalt?', answer: 'Europaische Lander haben sehr unterschiedliche Steuerstrukturen. Einige wie Danemark haben hohe Einkommensteuern aber niedrige Sozialabgaben. Andere wie Frankreich haben moderate Steuern aber hohe Sozialversicherungsbeitrage.' },
      { question: 'Kann ich den Rechner fur monatliche Gehaltsberechnungen verwenden?', answer: 'Der Rechner arbeitet mit dem Bruttojahresgehalt. Fur das monatliche Nettogehalt teilen Sie das Jahresergebnis durch 12. Beachten Sie, dass einige Lander 14 statt 12 Monatsgehalter zahlen.' },
    ],
  },
  es: {
    h1: 'Cuanto se llevara a casa despues de impuestos en Europa?',
    metaTitle: 'Calculadora de salario neto: sueldo neto en 15 paises de la UE | EuroSalary.eu',
    metaDesc: 'Calcule su salario neto despues de impuesto sobre la renta y seguridad social en 15 paises europeos. Utiliza los tramos fiscales 2026 para Alemania, Francia, Paises Bajos, Espana y mas.',
    home: 'Inicio',
    breadcrumbCalc: 'Calculadora',
    breadcrumb: 'Salario Neto',
    introAnswer: 'Nuestra calculadora de salario neto convierte instantaneamente su salario bruto anual en sueldo neto para 15 paises europeos. Aplica los tramos del impuesto sobre la renta y las tasas de seguridad social de 2026 para comparar lo que realmente conserva.',
    tldr: [
      'Cubre 15 paises de la UE con tramos fiscales 2026 y tasas de cotizaciones sociales',
      'Tres estados de declaracion: soltero, casado y casado con hijos',
      'Resultados instantaneos mostrando salario bruto, impuesto sobre la renta, seguridad social y salario neto',
    ],
    calcTitle: 'Calcule su salario neto',
    calcDesc: 'Seleccione un pais, introduzca su salario bruto anual y elija su estado civil. Los resultados se actualizan al instante.',
    countryLabel: 'Pais',
    countryPlaceholder: 'Seleccione un pais',
    grossLabel: 'Salario bruto anual',
    grossPlaceholder: '50000',
    statusLabel: 'Estado civil',
    statusSingle: 'Soltero/a',
    statusMarried: 'Casado/a',
    statusMarriedChildren: 'Casado/a con hijos',
    calculateBtn: 'Calcular salario neto',
    resultGross: 'Salario bruto',
    resultIncomeTax: 'Impuesto sobre la renta',
    resultSocial: 'Seguridad social',
    resultNet: 'Salario neto (a percibir)',
    resultTitle: 'Sus resultados',
    breakdownTitle: 'Desglose salarial',
    compareTitle: 'Como se compara con otros paises?',
    compareDesc: 'El mismo salario bruto produce un salario neto muy diferente en los distintos paises europeos. Los regimenes fiscales, las tasas de cotizacion social y las deducciones varian considerablemente. Use la calculadora con diferentes paises para comparar directamente.',
    disclaimerTitle: 'Aviso importante',
    disclaimerText: 'Esta calculadora proporciona estimaciones basadas en tramos fiscales simplificados de 2026 y tasas estandar de seguridad social. El salario neto real puede diferir debido a recargos locales, impuestos regionales, deducciones personales y contribuciones especificas del empleador. Consulte a un asesor fiscal local para calculos precisos.',
    faq: [
      { question: 'Que tan precisa es esta calculadora de salario neto?', answer: 'La calculadora utiliza tramos fiscales simplificados de 2026 y tasas estandar de cotizaciones sociales. Proporciona una estimacion fiable para planificacion, pero no tiene en cuenta recargos locales, impuestos religiosos o deducciones personales.' },
      { question: 'Que ano fiscal reflejan los tramos?', answer: 'Todos los tramos y tasas se basan en la legislacion 2026 publicada por las autoridades fiscales de cada pais. Actualizamos anualmente cuando se anuncian oficialmente las nuevas tasas.' },
      { question: 'El estado civil afecta al calculo?', answer: 'Si. En la mayoria de paises europeos, los casados se benefician de tributacion conjunta o splitting. El estado casado con hijos aplica deducciones adicionales por hijos donde corresponda.' },
      { question: 'Por que el mismo salario bruto da un neto muy diferente en distintos paises?', answer: 'Los paises europeos tienen estructuras fiscales muy diferentes. Algunos como Dinamarca tienen impuestos altos pero cotizaciones bajas. Otros como Francia tienen impuestos moderados pero cargas sociales elevadas.' },
      { question: 'Puedo usar esta calculadora para calculos mensuales?', answer: 'La calculadora trabaja con el salario bruto anual. Para estimar el ingreso neto mensual, divida el resultado anual por 12. Tenga en cuenta que algunos paises pagan 14 mensualidades en lugar de 12.' },
    ],
  },
};

const c = fb(i18n, lang);

const countries = [
  { code: 'DE', en: 'Germany', fr: 'Allemagne', de: 'Deutschland', es: 'Alemania' },
  { code: 'FR', en: 'France', fr: 'France', de: 'Frankreich', es: 'Francia' },
  { code: 'NL', en: 'Netherlands', fr: 'Pays-Bas', de: 'Niederlande', es: 'Paises Bajos' },
  { code: 'BE', en: 'Belgium', fr: 'Belgique', de: 'Belgien', es: 'Belgica' },
  { code: 'LU', en: 'Luxembourg', fr: 'Luxembourg', de: 'Luxemburg', es: 'Luxemburgo' },
  { code: 'AT', en: 'Austria', fr: 'Autriche', de: 'Osterreich', es: 'Austria' },
  { code: 'IE', en: 'Ireland', fr: 'Irlande', de: 'Irland', es: 'Irlanda' },
  { code: 'ES', en: 'Spain', fr: 'Espagne', de: 'Spanien', es: 'Espana' },
  { code: 'IT', en: 'Italy', fr: 'Italie', de: 'Italien', es: 'Italia' },
  { code: 'PT', en: 'Portugal', fr: 'Portugal', de: 'Portugal', es: 'Portugal' },
  { code: 'FI', en: 'Finland', fr: 'Finlande', de: 'Finnland', es: 'Finlandia' },
  { code: 'SE', en: 'Sweden', fr: 'Suede', de: 'Schweden', es: 'Suecia' },
  { code: 'DK', en: 'Denmark', fr: 'Danemark', de: 'Danemark', es: 'Dinamarca' },
  { code: 'PL', en: 'Poland', fr: 'Pologne', de: 'Polen', es: 'Polonia' },
  { code: 'CZ', en: 'Czech Republic', fr: 'Republique tcheque', de: 'Tschechien', es: 'Republica Checa' },
];

// --------------- Schema ---------------
const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: c.h1,
  description: c.metaDesc,
  url: `https://eurosalary.eu/${lang}/calculator/net-salary/`,
  inLanguage: lang,
  datePublished: '2026-04-04',
  dateModified: '2026-04-04',
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'EuroSalary.eu', url: 'https://eurosalary.eu' },
  publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'EuroSalary.eu', url: 'https://eurosalary.eu', logo: { '@type': 'ImageObject', url: 'https://eurosalary.eu/logo.svg' } },
};

const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: c.faq.map((item) => ({
    '@type': 'Question',
    name: item.question,
    acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: item.answer },
  })),
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title={c.metaTitle}
  description={c.metaDesc}
  datePublished="2026-04-04"
  dateModified="2026-04-04"
  schema={[articleSchema, faqSchema]}
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero__dots"></div>
    <div class="container page-hero__inner">
      <nav class="page-hero__breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href={`/${lang}/`}>{c.home}</a>
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined">chevron_right</span>
        <a href={`/${lang}/calculator/`}>{c.breadcrumbCalc}</a>
        <span class="material-symbols-outlined">chevron_right</span>
        <span class="page-hero__breadcrumbs-current">{c.breadcrumb}</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">{c.h1}</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__desc">{c.introAnswer}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container page-body">
    <!-- TL;DR -->
    <TLDRBox items={c.tldr} />

    <!-- Calculator -->
    <section class="section">
      <h2>{c.calcTitle}</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">{c.calcDesc}</p>

      <div class="calc-wrapper" id="netCalc">
        <div class="calc-form">
          <div class="calc-form__row">
            <div class="calc-form__field">
              <label for="calcCountry">{c.countryLabel}</label>
              <select id="calcCountry">
                <option value="" disabled selected>{c.countryPlaceholder}</option>
                {countries.map((country) => (
                  <option value={country.code}>{fb(country, lang)}</option>
                ))}
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-form__field">
              <label for="calcGross">{c.grossLabel}</label>
              <div class="calc-form__input-wrap">
                <span class="calc-form__currency">&euro;</span>
                <input type="number" id="calcGross" placeholder={c.grossPlaceholder} min="0" step="1000" />
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-form__row">
            <div class="calc-form__field">
              <label for="calcStatus">{c.statusLabel}</label>
              <select id="calcStatus">
                <option value="single">{c.statusSingle}</option>
                <option value="married">{c.statusMarried}</option>
                <option value="married_children">{c.statusMarriedChildren}</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-form__field calc-form__field--btn">
              <button type="button" id="calcBtn" class="calc-form__submit">{c.calculateBtn}</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Results (hidden until calculated) -->
        <div class="calc-results" id="calcResults" style="display:none;">
          <h3>{c.resultTitle}</h3>
          <div class="calc-results__grid">
            <div class="calc-results__item">
              <span class="calc-results__label">{c.resultGross}</span>
              <span class="calc-results__value" id="resGross">-</span>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-results__item calc-results__item--tax">
              <span class="calc-results__label">{c.resultIncomeTax}</span>
              <span class="calc-results__value" id="resTax">-</span>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-results__item calc-results__item--social">
              <span class="calc-results__label">{c.resultSocial}</span>
              <span class="calc-results__value" id="resSocial">-</span>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-results__item calc-results__item--net">
              <span class="calc-results__label">{c.resultNet}</span>
              <span class="calc-results__value" id="resNet">-</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Visual bar breakdown -->
          <h4>{c.breakdownTitle}</h4>
          <div class="calc-bar" id="calcBar">
            <div class="calc-bar__segment calc-bar__segment--tax" id="barTax">
              <span class="calc-bar__label" id="barTaxLabel">Tax</span>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-bar__segment calc-bar__segment--social" id="barSocial">
              <span class="calc-bar__label" id="barSocialLabel">Social</span>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-bar__segment calc-bar__segment--net" id="barNet">
              <span class="calc-bar__label" id="barNetLabel">Net</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Comparison -->
    <section class="section">
      <h2>{c.compareTitle}</h2>
      <p>{c.compareDesc}</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Disclaimer -->
    <section class="section disclaimer-section">
      <h2>{c.disclaimerTitle}</h2>
      <p>{c.disclaimerText}</p>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <FAQSection items={c.faq} />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const taxData: Record<string, { brackets: [number, number, number][]; social: number }> = {
    DE: { brackets: [[0, 11604, 0], [11604, 17006, 14], [17006, 66761, 24], [66761, 277826, 42], [277826, Infinity, 45]], social: 20.4 },
    FR: { brackets: [[0, 11294, 0], [11294, 28797, 11], [28797, 82341, 30], [82341, 177106, 41], [177106, Infinity, 45]], social: 22.2 },
    NL: { brackets: [[0, 38098, 9.32], [38098, 75518, 36.97], [75518, Infinity, 49.50]], social: 27.65 },
    BE: { brackets: [[0, 15820, 25], [15820, 27920, 40], [27920, 48320, 45], [48320, Infinity, 50]], social: 13.07 },
    LU: { brackets: [[0, 11850, 0], [11850, 13750, 8], [13750, 15750, 10], [15750, 17850, 12], [17850, 200004, 14], [200004, Infinity, 42]], social: 12.45 },
    AT: { brackets: [[0, 12816, 0], [12816, 20818, 20], [20818, 34513, 30], [34513, 66612, 40], [66612, 99266, 48], [99266, 1000000, 50], [1000000, Infinity, 55]], social: 18.12 },
    IE: { brackets: [[0, 42000, 20], [42000, Infinity, 40]], social: 4.0 },
    ES: { brackets: [[0, 12450, 19], [12450, 20200, 24], [20200, 35200, 30], [35200, 60000, 37], [60000, 300000, 45], [300000, Infinity, 47]], social: 6.35 },
    IT: { brackets: [[0, 28000, 23], [28000, 50000, 35], [50000, Infinity, 43]], social: 9.49 },
    PT: { brackets: [[0, 7703, 14.5], [7703, 11623, 21], [11623, 16472, 26.5], [16472, 21321, 28.5], [21321, 27146, 35], [27146, 39791, 37], [39791, 51997, 43.5], [51997, 81199, 45], [81199, Infinity, 48]], social: 11.0 },
    FI: { brackets: [[0, 19900, 0], [19900, 29700, 12.64], [29700, 49000, 17.64], [49000, 85800, 21.14], [85800, Infinity, 31.64]], social: 10.18 },
    SE: { brackets: [[0, 46200, 0], [46200, 66800, 20], [66800, Infinity, 25]], social: 7.0 },
    DK: { brackets: [[0, 46700, 12.09], [46700, 552500, 15.09], [552500, Infinity, 15.09]], social: 8.0 },
    PL: { brackets: [[0, 30000, 0], [30000, 120000, 12], [120000, Infinity, 32]], social: 13.71 },
    CZ: { brackets: [[0, 1935552, 15], [1935552, Infinity, 23]], social: 11.0 },
  };

  function calculateTax(gross: number, brackets: [number, number, number][]): number {
    let tax = 0;
    for (const [low, high, rate] of brackets) {
      if (gross <= low) break;
      const taxable = Math.min(gross, high) - low;
      tax += taxable * (rate / 100);
    }
    return tax;
  }

  function calculate() {
    const countryEl = document.getElementById('calcCountry') as HTMLSelectElement;
    const grossEl = document.getElementById('calcGross') as HTMLInputElement;
    const statusEl = document.getElementById('calcStatus') as HTMLSelectElement;
    const resultsEl = document.getElementById('calcResults') as HTMLElement;

    const country = countryEl.value;
    const gross = parseFloat(grossEl.value);
    const status = statusEl.value;

    if (!country || !gross || gross <= 0) return;

    const data = taxData[country];
    if (!data) return;

    // Apply filing status adjustments
    let taxableIncome = gross;
    let taxReduction = 1.0;
    if (status === 'married') {
      // Simplified: married filers get income splitting (divide by 2, calc tax, multiply by 2)
      taxableIncome = gross / 2;
      taxReduction = 2.0;
    } else if (status === 'married_children') {
      // Simplified: family quotient (divide by 2.5, calc tax, multiply by 2.5)
      taxableIncome = gross / 2.5;
      taxReduction = 2.5;
    }

    const incomeTax = Math.round(calculateTax(taxableIncome, data.brackets) * taxReduction);
    const socialSecurity = Math.round(gross * (data.social / 100));
    const netSalary = gross - incomeTax - socialSecurity;

    const fmt = (n: number) => new Intl.NumberFormat('en-EU', { style: 'currency', currency: 'EUR', minimumFractionDigits: 0, maximumFractionDigits: 0 }).format(n);

    (document.getElementById('resGross') as HTMLElement).textContent = fmt(gross);
    (document.getElementById('resTax') as HTMLElement).textContent = '-' + fmt(incomeTax);
    (document.getElementById('resSocial') as HTMLElement).textContent = '-' + fmt(socialSecurity);
    (document.getElementById('resNet') as HTMLElement).textContent = fmt(netSalary);

    // Bar chart
    const taxPct = (incomeTax / gross) * 100;
    const socialPct = (socialSecurity / gross) * 100;
    const netPct = (netSalary / gross) * 100;

    (document.getElementById('barTax') as HTMLElement).style.width = taxPct + '%';
    (document.getElementById('barSocial') as HTMLElement).style.width = socialPct + '%';
    (document.getElementById('barNet') as HTMLElement).style.width = netPct + '%';

    (document.getElementById('barTaxLabel') as HTMLElement).textContent = Math.round(taxPct) + '%';
    (document.getElementById('barSocialLabel') as HTMLElement).textContent = Math.round(socialPct) + '%';
    (document.getElementById('barNetLabel') as HTMLElement).textContent = Math.round(netPct) + '%';

    resultsEl.style.display = 'block';
  }

  document.getElementById('calcBtn')?.addEventListener('click', calculate);

  // Also calculate on Enter key in gross input
  document.getElementById('calcGross')?.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
    if ((e as KeyboardEvent).key === 'Enter') calculate();
  });
</script>

